President Obama announced his intent to nominate four individuals to key administration posts: Robert M. Groves as Director of the Bureau of the Census, Victor M. Mendez as Administrator of the Federal Highway Administration, Peter H. Appel as Administrator of the Research and Innovative Technology Administration, and John Q. Easton as Director of the Institute of Education Sciences. Groves is currently the Director of the University of Michigan Survey Research Center and has extensive experience in surveys and statistics. Mendez previously served as the Director of the Arizona Department of Transportation and has expertise in transportation funding and infrastructure. Appel is a Principal with A.T. Kearney and has over 20 years of experience in transportation consulting. Easton is currently the Executive Director of The Consortium on Chicago School Research and has held various positions in education research and evaluation.